03.22287v1", "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1134934", "oai:arXiv.org:2603.24680v1", "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1135118", "oai:arXiv.org:2604.00086v1"], "today_date": "2026-04-28", "today_news": [{"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1136438", "title": "The Download: DeepSeek\u2019s latest AI breakthrough, and the race to build world models", "summary": "This is today&#8217;s edition of The Download, our weekday newsletter that provides a daily dose of what&#8217;s going on in the world of technology. Three reasons why DeepSeek\u2019s new model matters On Friday, Chinese AI firm DeepSeek released a preview of V4, its long-awaited new flagship model. Nota...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/27/1136438/the-download-deepseek-v4-ai-world-models/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 9}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=34880", "title": "OpenAI and Microsoft rewrite their deal: no more exclusivity, no more AGI clause", "summary": "OpenAI is free to distribute its products through any cloud provider, Microsoft loses its exclusive license to OpenAI's technology, and the controversial AGI clause is gone.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/openai-and-microsoft-rewrite-their-deal-no-more-exclusivity-no-more-agi-clause/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 6}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=34871", "title": "China blocks Meta's $2 billion acquisition of AI startup Manus", "summary": "Beijing orders the unwinding of the already completed acquisition. The move comes amid intensifying technological rivalry between the US and China.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/china-blocks-metas-2-billion-acquisition-of-ai-startup-manus/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 6}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1136466", "title": "Elon Musk and Sam Altman are going to court over OpenAI\u2019s future", "summary": "After a yearslong legal feud, Elon Musk and OpenAI CEO Sam Altman are heading to trial this week in Northern California in a case that could have sweeping consequences. Ahead of OpenAI\u2019s highly anticipated IPO, the court could rule on whether the company is allowed to exist as a for-profit enterpris...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/27/1136466/elon-musk-and-sam-altman-are-going-to-court-over-openais-future/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 5}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=34877", "title": "Sam Altman outlines five principles that double as justification for OpenAI's business decisions", "summary": "OpenAI's CEO has laid out five guiding principles for the company's future work. They also serve as a rationale for some of OpenAI's more unconventional business moves.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/sam-altman-outlines-five-principles-that-double-as-justification-for-openais-business-decisions/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 4}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1136456", "title": "The missing step between hype and profit", "summary": "This story originally appeared in The Algorithm, our weekly newsletter on AI. To get stories like this in your inbox first, sign up here. In February, I picked up a flyer at an anti-AI march in London. I can\u2019t say for sure whether or not its writers meant to riff on South Park\u2019s underpants gnomes. B...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/27/1136456/the-missing-step-between-hype-and-profit/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 2}, {"id": "https://www.technologyreview.com/?p=1136322", "title": "Rebuilding the data stack for AI", "summary": "Artificial intelligence may be dominating boardroom agendas, but many enterprises are discovering that the biggest obstacle to meaningful adoption is the state of their data. While consumer-facing AI tools have dazzled users with speed and ease, enterprise leaders are discovering that deploying AI a...", "link": "https://www.technologyreview.com/2026/04/27/1136322/rebuilding-the-data-stack-for-ai/", "source": "MIT Tech Review", "image": null, "score": 2}, {"id": "https://the-decoder.com/?p=34874", "title": "Meta wants to power AI data centers with solar energy from space", "summary": "Meta has signed a deal with startup Overview Energy for up to 1 gigawatt of space-based solar power. The only catch: the technology doesn't exist yet.", "link": "https://the-decoder.com/meta-wants-to-power-ai-data-centers-with-solar-energy-from-space/", "source": "The Decoder", "image": null, "score": 2}], "today_tech": [{"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2604.22822v1", "title": "DO-Bench: An Attributable Benchmark for Diagnosing Object Hallucination in Vision-Language Models", "summary": "Abstract: Object level hallucination remains a central reliability challenge for vision language models (VLMs), particularly in binary object existence verification. Existing benchmarks emphasize aggregate accuracy but rarely disentangle whether errors stem from perceptual limitations or from the in...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22822", "source": "arXiv CV", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.22822v1/2604.22822v1/x1.png", "score": 15}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2604.22821v1", "title": "Audio2Tool: Bridging Spoken Language Understanding and Function Calling", "summary": "Abstract: Voice assistants increasingly rely on Speech Language Models (SpeechLMs) to interpret spoken queries and execute complex tasks, yet existing benchmarks lack domain breadth, acoustic diversity, and compositional reasoning complexity to evaluate tool-calling performance. We introduce Audio2T...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22821", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.22821v1/2604.22821v1/x1.png", "score": 13}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2604.23586v1", "title": "Talker-T2AV: Joint Talking Audio-Video Generation with Autoregressive Diffusion Modeling", "summary": "Abstract: Joint audio-video generation models have shown that unified generation yields stronger cross-modal coherence than cascaded approaches. However, existing models couple modalities throughout denoising via pervasive attention, treating high-level semantics and low-level details in a fully ent...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.23586", "source": "arXiv Audio & Speech", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.23586v1/2604.23586v1/x1.png", "score": 13}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2604.22779v1", "title": "KARL: Mitigating Hallucinations in LLMs via Knowledge-Boundary-Aware Reinforcement Learning", "summary": "Abstract: Enabling large language models (LLMs) to appropriately abstain from answering questions beyond their knowledge is crucial for mitigating hallucinations. While existing reinforcement learning methods foster autonomous abstention, they often compromise answer accuracy because their static re...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22779", "source": "arXiv CS ML", "image": null, "score": 12}, {"id": "oai:arXiv.org:2604.22783v1", "title": "Parameter Efficiency Is Not Memory Efficiency: Rethinking Fine-Tuning for On-Device LLM Adaptation", "summary": "Abstract: Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT) has become the standard for adapting large language models (LLMs). In this work we challenge the wide-spread assumption that parameter efficiency equates memory efficiency and on-device adaptability. We show that this is not true - while methods like ...", "link": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.22783", "source": "arXiv CS ML", "image": "https://arxiv.org/html/2604.22783v1/2604.22783v1/x1.png", "score": 11}]}